SIMPLE: indemnify
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indemnify
<hw>In*dem"ni*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Indemnified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Indemnifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>indemnis</ets> unhurt (<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>damnum</ets> hurt,
damage) + <ets>-fy</ets>. Cf. <er>Damn</er>,
<er>Damnify</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To save harmless; to secure against loss or damage;
to insure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The states must at last engage to the merchants here that they
will <qex>indemnify</qex> them from all that shall fall out.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Temple.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make restitution or compensation for, as for that
which is lost; to make whole; to reimburse; to compensate.</def>
<rj><au>Beattie.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indemnity</ent>⟦br⟧
